00:16:12.900 --> 00:16:14.640 align:middle line:90%
Those have been cast off.

00:16:14.640 --> 00:16:17.670 align:middle line:84%
Each person for themselves
to figure this stuff out now.

00:16:17.670 --> 00:16:20.310 align:middle line:90%
And I'm an observer.

00:16:20.310 --> 00:16:21.600 align:middle line:90%
I've always been an observer.

00:16:21.600 --> 00:16:23.190 align:middle line:90%
I'm kind of an outsider.

00:16:23.190 --> 00:16:25.770 align:middle line:90%
So I just watch people a lot.

00:16:25.770 --> 00:16:30.740 align:middle line:84%
And first of all, trying to
go against human nature never

00:16:30.740 --> 00:16:31.910 align:middle line:90%
bodes well.

00:16:31.910 --> 00:16:33.470 align:middle line:90%
It's like the polyamory thing.

00:16:33.470 --> 00:16:36.210 align:middle line:84%
By and large, I think there's
a new show on Netflix where,

00:16:36.210 --> 00:16:37.010 align:middle line:90%
same thing.

00:16:37.010 --> 00:16:39.120 align:middle line:84%
And then the woman starts
having a relationship

00:16:39.120 --> 00:16:39.920 align:middle line:90%
with another guy.

00:16:39.920 --> 00:16:42.740 align:middle line:84%
And then she just says, OK,
he's the one and she's gone.

00:16:42.740 --> 00:16:46.820 align:middle line:84%
Because there has been this
imperative within women

00:16:46.820 --> 00:16:48.560 align:middle line:84%
to be able to
gather, and nurture,

00:16:48.560 --> 00:16:50.690 align:middle line:90%
and bond, and care for.

00:16:50.690 --> 00:16:52.100 align:middle line:90%
I mean that is whether--

00:16:52.100 --> 00:16:54.600 align:middle line:84%
and through paths of
incarnation, if you're a male,

00:16:54.600 --> 00:16:55.640 align:middle line:90%
you have one directive.

00:16:55.640 --> 00:17:00.110 align:middle line:84%
If you're a female, and both
have each of the other in there

00:17:00.110 --> 00:17:02.870 align:middle line:84%
to one percentage
or another, there

00:17:02.870 --> 00:17:06.230 align:middle line:84%
are still classic kinds of
imperatives that happen.

00:17:06.230 --> 00:17:09.800 align:middle line:84%
And women generally
tend to want to bond

00:17:09.800 --> 00:17:14.150 align:middle line:84%
and generally tend to
want to care or nurture.

00:17:14.150 --> 00:17:19.069 align:middle line:84%
Now for the first
time, I'm seeing it,

00:17:19.069 --> 00:17:21.270 align:middle line:90%
it appears to be changing.

00:17:21.270 --> 00:17:23.839 align:middle line:84%
But I don't know if it's
just appearances because

00:17:23.839 --> 00:17:28.310 align:middle line:84%
of the backlash of men coming
out from under patriarchy

00:17:28.310 --> 00:17:30.735 align:middle line:84%
and honoring strong women
because they're there.

00:17:30.735 --> 00:17:32.180 align:middle line:90%
They're graduating from college.

00:17:32.180 --> 00:17:33.800 align:middle line:90%
They're getting the top jobs.

00:17:33.800 --> 00:17:36.230 align:middle line:84%
Women are now out
there doing the things

00:17:36.230 --> 00:17:37.700 align:middle line:90%
that men traditionally did.

00:17:37.700 --> 00:17:39.750 align:middle line:90%
We know that.

00:17:39.750 --> 00:17:42.060 align:middle line:84%
But on a
psychospiritual level, I

00:17:42.060 --> 00:17:45.330 align:middle line:84%
want to know your perception
of what that feels

00:17:45.330 --> 00:17:48.860 align:middle line:90%
like from your own experience.

00:17:48.860 --> 00:17:51.770 align:middle line:84%
Because you were
raised to respect women

00:17:51.770 --> 00:17:54.140 align:middle line:84%
and raised with
strong women, but now

00:17:54.140 --> 00:17:56.540 align:middle line:84%
we're seeing toxic
femininity emerging.

00:17:56.540 --> 00:17:59.270 align:middle line:84%
Some really nasty, mean
behavior, horrible stuff

00:17:59.270 --> 00:18:01.280 align:middle line:84%
coming out, which
you can understand

00:18:01.280 --> 00:18:03.320 align:middle line:84%
after bursting out
from under patriarchy

00:18:03.320 --> 00:18:05.710 align:middle line:90%
after thousands of years.

00:18:05.710 --> 00:18:08.200 align:middle line:84%
That's a long way
to say, what's up?

00:18:08.200 --> 00:18:09.000 align:middle line:90%
>>MARCUS: Yeah.

00:18:09.000 --> 00:18:12.103 align:middle line:84%
Well, every repressed action,
every action of repression,

00:18:12.103 --> 00:18:14.520 align:middle line:84%
I should say, any time we're
trying to push something down

00:18:14.520 --> 00:18:17.740 align:middle line:84%
it's basically spring loading
a variety of different things.

00:18:17.740 --> 00:18:20.940 align:middle line:84%
And so you look at it and what
has been suppressed in men?

00:18:20.940 --> 00:18:23.910 align:middle line:84%
Well men's femininity
has been suppressed.

00:18:23.910 --> 00:18:25.830 align:middle line:90%
Don't you cry.

00:18:25.830 --> 00:18:26.920 align:middle line:90%
Dry those tears.

00:18:26.920 --> 00:18:28.680 align:middle line:90%
Suck it up, bucko.

00:18:28.680 --> 00:18:30.130 align:middle line:90%
Like get back in there.

00:18:30.130 --> 00:18:32.850 align:middle line:84%
This kind of like you got to
be hard, you got to be strong.

00:18:32.850 --> 00:18:33.240 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:18:33.240 --> 00:18:34.323 align:middle line:90%
So what's been suppressed?

00:18:34.323 --> 00:18:37.297 align:middle line:84%
Well that soft like it hurts,
and I just want to cry,

00:18:37.297 --> 00:18:38.130 align:middle line:90%
and I want to share.

00:18:38.130 --> 00:18:38.690 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Or hug.

00:18:38.690 --> 00:18:39.490 align:middle line:90%
>>MARCUS: Exactly.

00:18:39.490 --> 00:18:41.160 align:middle line:90%
So that's coming out.

00:18:41.160 --> 00:18:43.380 align:middle line:84%
And you're seeing a
lot of men exploring

00:18:43.380 --> 00:18:46.530 align:middle line:84%
like a deep exploration
of their feminine side.

00:18:46.530 --> 00:18:49.590 align:middle line:84%
And on the female side,
what's been repressed?

00:18:49.590 --> 00:18:53.640 align:middle line:84%
Well, that go get them, that I'm
going to go get the best job,

00:18:53.640 --> 00:18:54.480 align:middle line:90%
do the best thing.

00:18:54.480 --> 00:18:58.440 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to do everything
that I can to just conquer out

00:18:58.440 --> 00:18:59.340 align:middle line:90%
in this world.

00:18:59.340 --> 00:19:01.000 align:middle line:90%
That's been suppressed as well.

00:19:01.000 --> 00:19:02.412 align:middle line:90%
So you're seeing that rise up.

00:19:02.412 --> 00:19:03.870 align:middle line:84%
And those are the
natural elements.

00:19:03.870 --> 00:19:06.120 align:middle line:84%
But it's not just those
elements that come,

00:19:06.120 --> 00:19:07.890 align:middle line:90%
there's the other aspects--

00:19:07.890 --> 00:19:10.080 align:middle line:84%
the frustration, the
resentments, the angers--

00:19:10.080 --> 00:19:12.940 align:middle line:84%
that are also coming
out in different ways.

00:19:12.940 --> 00:19:15.840 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's
really what we're seeing.

00:19:15.840 --> 00:19:17.520 align:middle line:84%
But where it's
heading, ultimately,

00:19:17.520 --> 00:19:20.280 align:middle line:90%
is we're finding equilibrium.

00:19:20.280 --> 00:19:22.630 align:middle line:84%
A lot of the pressure
is being released.

00:19:22.630 --> 00:19:26.160 align:middle line:84%
And as the pressure is
released, both positive aspects

00:19:26.160 --> 00:19:28.920 align:middle line:84%
and toxic aspects are
springing forward.

00:19:28.920 --> 00:19:31.230 align:middle line:84%
But I think that's
the necessary reaction

00:19:31.230 --> 00:19:33.930 align:middle line:84%
to go back and find
the balance as we

00:19:33.930 --> 00:19:35.820 align:middle line:84%
take the lid off
of everything, take

00:19:35.820 --> 00:19:37.362 align:middle line:90%
all the spring loading off.

00:19:37.362 --> 00:19:38.820 align:middle line:84%
And what I think,
ultimately, we're

00:19:38.820 --> 00:19:40.560 align:middle line:90%
going to find is real freedom.

00:19:40.560 --> 00:19:44.130 align:middle line:84%
Freedom to express not only
one aspect of the self,

00:19:44.130 --> 00:19:46.080 align:middle line:90%
but the entirety of who we are.

00:19:46.080 --> 00:19:49.950 align:middle line:84%
Which is our birthright, we
should be able to both cry

00:19:49.950 --> 00:19:52.860 align:middle line:84%
and then hold boldly
at the helm of a ship

00:19:52.860 --> 00:19:55.470 align:middle line:84%
in the middle of a storm,
and smile at the clouds,

00:19:55.470 --> 00:20:00.360 align:middle line:84%
and say do your worst, and also
curl up in the fetal position,

00:20:00.360 --> 00:20:03.240 align:middle line:84%
and have our head stroked
or stroke someone's head,

00:20:03.240 --> 00:20:05.200 align:middle line:90%
and weep.

00:20:05.200 --> 00:20:08.170 align:middle line:84%
Both of those aspects,
the warrior and the poet,

00:20:08.170 --> 00:20:10.920 align:middle line:84%
this is where I began with my
podcast platform, the "Warrior

00:20:10.920 --> 00:20:11.730 align:middle line:90%
Poet Project."

00:20:11.730 --> 00:20:15.000 align:middle line:84%
This idea of being both is,
I think, really important.

00:20:15.000 --> 00:20:18.930 align:middle line:84%
And for women the same,
that strong, loving, soft,

00:20:18.930 --> 00:20:23.490 align:middle line:84%
compassionate nurturer and
that ferocious mother lion.

00:20:23.490 --> 00:20:26.820 align:middle line:84%
All of those things should
be celebrated, revered.

00:20:26.820 --> 00:20:31.470 align:middle line:84%
What needs to be made aware
of is the repressed, still

00:20:31.470 --> 00:20:36.000 align:middle line:84%
repressed aspects, those
shadow aspects of the anger,

00:20:36.000 --> 00:20:37.337 align:middle line:90%
what we call the toxicity.

00:20:37.337 --> 00:20:38.670 align:middle line:90%
Those things we're not aware of.

00:20:38.670 --> 00:20:40.170 align:middle line:90%
Those dark impulses.

00:20:40.170 --> 00:20:42.420 align:middle line:84%
And it's not further
repression of those,

00:20:42.420 --> 00:20:45.780 align:middle line:84%
it's actually seeing
them, acknowledging them,

00:20:45.780 --> 00:20:47.190 align:middle line:90%
loving that they exist.

00:20:47.190 --> 00:20:50.190 align:middle line:84%
And it's actually the love
that allows them to soften.

00:20:50.190 --> 00:20:53.430 align:middle line:84%
Because if you judge them,
then there's going to be shame.

00:20:53.430 --> 00:20:55.390 align:middle line:84%
And the shame is going
to obscure your view.

00:20:55.390 --> 00:20:57.150 align:middle line:84%
And they're going to
remain in the shadow.

00:20:57.150 --> 00:21:00.810 align:middle line:84%
Whereas an acknowledged dark
impulse, you can manage,

00:21:00.810 --> 00:21:02.970 align:middle line:84%
but something that's in
the shadow will manage you.

00:21:02.970 --> 00:21:04.440 align:middle line:90%
It will overcome you.

00:21:04.440 --> 00:21:07.080 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So is your
own personal experience

00:21:07.080 --> 00:21:11.250 align:middle line:84%
that when the women who are
just now allowing the anger out

00:21:11.250 --> 00:21:13.985 align:middle line:84%
after repression-- and
you can call it past life,

00:21:13.985 --> 00:21:15.360 align:middle line:84%
you can call it
ancestral memory.

00:21:15.360 --> 00:21:17.910 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't really matter
where you look for it.

00:21:17.910 --> 00:21:19.110 align:middle line:90%
It's in the field.

00:21:19.110 --> 00:21:21.720 align:middle line:84%
Is your experience
that once the women

00:21:21.720 --> 00:21:23.760 align:middle line:90%
feel they have permission--

00:21:23.760 --> 00:21:25.500 align:middle line:84%
because that's a
big one with women--

00:21:25.500 --> 00:21:28.530 align:middle line:84%
to be their worst,
give you their worst

00:21:28.530 --> 00:21:31.110 align:middle line:84%
and you're still
standing there, does

00:21:31.110 --> 00:21:35.395 align:middle line:84%
that seem in your observation
to have freed something in them?

00:21:35.395 --> 00:21:36.270 align:middle line:90%
>>MARCUS: Absolutely.

00:21:36.270 --> 00:21:38.640 align:middle line:84%
And I have a very
personal experience

00:21:38.640 --> 00:21:40.470 align:middle line:90%
with this with my wife Vylana.

00:21:40.470 --> 00:21:43.650 align:middle line:84%
She is the kindest,
sweetest, most loving woman

00:21:43.650 --> 00:21:44.640 align:middle line:90%
I've ever known.

00:21:44.640 --> 00:21:46.080 align:middle line:90%
I mean it's really incredible.

00:21:46.080 --> 00:21:49.830 align:middle line:84%
But she has a dark,
Kali goddess aspect.

00:21:49.830 --> 00:21:55.110 align:middle line:84%
And it is absolutely
impressive, I have to say.

00:21:55.110 --> 00:21:57.540 align:middle line:84%
I mean I have never been
with someone who can--

00:21:57.540 --> 00:22:01.230 align:middle line:84%
when we would get in these
type of conflicts over nothing,

00:22:01.230 --> 00:22:04.050 align:middle line:84%
really, she would find
a way to put me in a box

00:22:04.050 --> 00:22:06.300 align:middle line:84%
where I couldn't say anything
because everything would

00:22:06.300 --> 00:22:08.020 align:middle line:90%
turn right back around on me.

00:22:08.020 --> 00:22:10.320 align:middle line:84%
And then the box would
get smaller, and smaller,

00:22:10.320 --> 00:22:12.540 align:middle line:84%
and smaller until I
was just floundering

00:22:12.540 --> 00:22:13.890 align:middle line:90%
with nothing to say.

00:22:13.890 --> 00:22:15.480 align:middle line:90%
And then it was over.

00:22:15.480 --> 00:22:18.540 align:middle line:10%
And I was like I
just got dominated.

00:22:18.540 --> 00:22:21.270 align:middle line:10%
And so we had one of
these experiences.

00:22:21.270 --> 00:22:25.170 align:middle line:84%
And we took some space and
went our separate ways.

00:22:25.170 --> 00:22:28.290 align:middle line:84%
And she came back expecting--
she felt really guilty

00:22:28.290 --> 00:22:31.200 align:middle line:84%
about this, because she's aware
of that pattern, her ability

00:22:31.200 --> 00:22:32.820 align:middle line:90%
to go to that level.

00:22:32.820 --> 00:22:35.490 align:middle line:90%
And she goes that was awful.

00:22:35.490 --> 00:22:37.650 align:middle line:84%
And I go, no, it wasn't,
that was awesome.

00:22:37.650 --> 00:22:40.170 align:middle line:84%
Like that was just
impressive that you were

00:22:40.170 --> 00:22:41.940 align:middle line:90%
able to summon such a force.

00:22:41.940 --> 00:22:45.480 align:middle line:84%
And I'm just in awe that
you have that within you.

00:22:45.480 --> 00:22:49.440 align:middle line:84%
And you could just see all of
these years of shame soften.

00:22:49.440 --> 00:22:51.990 align:middle line:84%
And since that
moment, she's really

00:22:51.990 --> 00:22:53.940 align:middle line:84%
owned, and kind of
loved, and embodied

00:22:53.940 --> 00:22:55.170 align:middle line:90%
that that's within her.

00:22:55.170 --> 00:22:58.080 align:middle line:84%
And it hasn't had any
need to come out, not

00:22:58.080 --> 00:22:59.640 align:middle line:90%
a single other time since.

00:22:59.640 --> 00:23:02.025 align:middle line:84%
It was the love and
reverence for that

00:23:02.025 --> 00:23:05.980 align:middle line:84%
that allowed it to actually
move through and integrate fully

00:23:05.980 --> 00:23:06.790 align:middle line:90%
into her.

00:23:06.790 --> 00:23:09.128 align:middle line:84%
And it's been a huge-- and
she would say the same thing,

00:23:09.128 --> 00:23:10.420 align:middle line:90%
that was a huge moment for her.

00:23:10.420 --> 00:23:12.610 align:middle line:84%
So as we see this
in the collective,

00:23:12.610 --> 00:23:13.880 align:middle line:90%
too, it's the same thing.

00:23:13.880 --> 00:23:17.170 align:middle line:84%
The more that we can
love instead of judge--

00:23:17.170 --> 00:23:19.390 align:middle line:84%
we have to protect
ourselves, I understand.

00:23:19.390 --> 00:23:20.680 align:middle line:90%
Have your boundaries.

00:23:20.680 --> 00:23:22.810 align:middle line:84%
But nonetheless if
the undercurrent

00:23:22.810 --> 00:23:26.200 align:middle line:84%
of those boundaries is love,
and reverence, and respect,

00:23:26.200 --> 00:23:28.827 align:middle line:84%
that's what's going to
allow this thing to heal.

00:23:28.827 --> 00:23:30.410 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I absolutely
agree with you.

00:23:30.410 --> 00:23:34.750 align:middle line:84%
And I remember over
the course of years

00:23:34.750 --> 00:23:37.540 align:middle line:84%
when I was trying to find a
relationship-- because I'm

00:23:37.540 --> 00:23:38.620 align:middle line:90%
a bit of an oddball.

00:23:38.620 --> 00:23:39.890 align:middle line:90%
I'm not an easy fit.

00:23:39.890 --> 00:23:45.280 align:middle line:84%
And one of my secret wishes was
that I could just be my worst

00:23:45.280 --> 00:23:47.710 align:middle line:84%
and someone would still
be standing there.

00:23:47.710 --> 00:23:49.900 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:23:49.900 --> 00:23:52.060 align:middle line:84%
And I am in that
relationship now.

00:23:52.060 --> 00:23:54.447 align:middle line:84%
My husband Zeus and I have
that, because he's like you--

00:23:54.447 --> 00:23:55.780 align:middle line:90%
>>MARCUS: The right name for it.

00:23:55.780 --> 00:23:56.960 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, yeah, right?

00:23:56.960 --> 00:23:58.540 align:middle line:90%
I have a lot of electricity.

00:23:58.540 --> 00:24:02.350 align:middle line:84%
And again though but he's
secure enough and who he is

00:24:02.350 --> 00:24:06.412 align:middle line:84%
as a person that to watch that
energy if we get in conflict

00:24:06.412 --> 00:24:08.620 align:middle line:84%
with each other-- because
I don't like being cornered

00:24:08.620 --> 00:24:09.970 align:middle line:90%
so then I'll fight back--

00:24:09.970 --> 00:24:12.400 align:middle line:84%
to watch that emerge
and at the end,

00:24:12.400 --> 00:24:13.870 align:middle line:90%
he doesn't take it personally.

00:24:13.870 --> 00:24:17.810 align:middle line:84%
I'm shaken up when that
happens but he's not.

00:24:17.810 --> 00:24:20.860 align:middle line:84%
It's just like, good,
I'm glad you really

00:24:20.860 --> 00:24:22.570 align:middle line:90%
got to express yourself.

00:24:22.570 --> 00:24:28.180 align:middle line:84%
And that is a very hard thing
to actually connect with,

00:24:28.180 --> 00:24:32.000 align:middle line:84%
because a lot of men are very
intimidated by that ferocity.

00:24:32.000 --> 00:24:32.800 align:middle line:90%
>>MARCUS: Sure.

00:24:32.800 --> 00:24:38.200 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I'm a Metal Tiger in
Chinese, I guess you call it--

00:24:38.200 --> 00:24:39.980 align:middle line:90%
not astrology, whatever it is.

00:24:39.980 --> 00:24:42.340 align:middle line:84%
And so someone hurts
someone I love,

00:24:42.340 --> 00:24:44.660 align:middle line:90%
I will go and stand up for them.

00:24:44.660 --> 00:24:46.542 align:middle line:84%
But a lot of men are
very, very intimidated

00:24:46.542 --> 00:24:49.000 align:middle line:84%
by that at this point still
because we haven't crossed over

00:24:49.000 --> 00:24:51.610 align:middle line:84%
from the time where women
kind of cowered and waited

00:24:51.610 --> 00:24:54.880 align:middle line:84%
for permission on subtle levels
that we don't even understand.

00:24:54.880 --> 00:24:56.468 align:middle line:90%
It's so embedded in us.

00:24:56.468 --> 00:24:58.510 align:middle line:84%
So it's really up to the
guys to kind of stand up

00:24:58.510 --> 00:25:00.580 align:middle line:84%
and say, OK, gulp,
I can take it.

00:25:00.580 --> 00:25:01.450 align:middle line:90%
>>MARCUS: Yeah.

00:25:01.450 --> 00:25:05.270 align:middle line:84%
I think that ability to
look at any force of chaos,

00:25:05.270 --> 00:25:06.645 align:middle line:84%
whether it's the
chaos of nature,

00:25:06.645 --> 00:25:09.520 align:middle line:84%
or whether it's a virus,
or whether it's a person,

00:25:09.520 --> 00:25:12.100 align:middle line:84%
or whether it's an animal and
have that awe, and reverence,

00:25:12.100 --> 00:25:15.540 align:middle line:84%
and respect without that
fear-based desire to dominate

00:25:15.540 --> 00:25:16.340 align:middle line:90%
and control--

00:25:16.340 --> 00:25:20.305 align:middle line:84%
which I think has permeated our
entire psyche and our culture.

00:25:20.305 --> 00:25:22.930 align:middle line:90%
Ahh, there's danger and chaos.

00:25:22.930 --> 00:25:25.540 align:middle line:84%
Instead of respecting and
finding our accord with it

00:25:25.540 --> 00:25:28.940 align:middle line:84%
and trusting ourself, we try
to dominate and control it.

00:25:28.940 --> 00:25:31.330 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's been
the impulse that we've had

00:25:31.330 --> 00:25:32.720 align:middle line:90%
and continue to have.

00:25:32.720 --> 00:25:34.570 align:middle line:84%
And really what we
want to look at--

00:25:34.570 --> 00:25:37.450 align:middle line:84%
a great symbol, the symbol
I always look to is you

00:25:37.450 --> 00:25:40.240 align:middle line:84%
look at any statue of Kali
or any depiction of Kali

00:25:40.240 --> 00:25:43.510 align:middle line:84%
and she's got the severed
heads of the men representing

00:25:43.510 --> 00:25:46.150 align:middle line:84%
the egos that she's
destroyed, and severed arms.

00:25:46.150 --> 00:25:47.740 align:middle line:90%
And she's got her tongue out.

00:25:47.740 --> 00:25:49.540 align:middle line:90%
She's got her wild--

00:25:49.540 --> 00:25:52.180 align:middle line:84%
they call her the dark
goddess with her wild hair

00:25:52.180 --> 00:25:54.400 align:middle line:90%
and the bloody sabers.

00:25:54.400 --> 00:25:56.260 align:middle line:84%
And what's Shiva
doing, the expression

00:25:56.260 --> 00:25:57.610 align:middle line:90%
of the divine masculine?

00:25:57.610 --> 00:26:00.190 align:middle line:84%
He's just laying back
looking back at her

00:26:00.190 --> 00:26:02.350 align:middle line:90%
like ain't she beautiful?

00:26:02.350 --> 00:26:03.190 align:middle line:90%
Ain't she beautiful?

00:26:03.190 --> 00:26:06.490 align:middle line:84%
And that's the divine
masculine-- hold all of it,

00:26:06.490 --> 00:26:09.740 align:middle line:84%
every bit of it,
and just say, wow.

00:26:09.740 --> 00:26:12.790 align:middle line:84%
And if we can get
there allowing--

00:26:12.790 --> 00:26:15.020 align:middle line:84%
and all of us can be
an aspect of that,

00:26:15.020 --> 00:26:17.410 align:middle line:84%
but if we can allow
that to come forward,

00:26:17.410 --> 00:26:19.355 align:middle line:84%
I think that's the
healing, loving energy

00:26:19.355 --> 00:26:20.230 align:middle line:90%
that the world needs.

00:26:20.230 --> 00:26:21.688 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Absolutely
the women have

00:26:21.688 --> 00:26:23.170 align:middle line:84%
to blow off steam
after thousands

00:26:23.170 --> 00:26:24.695 align:middle line:90%
of years of this suppression.

00:26:24.695 --> 00:26:25.495 align:middle line:90%
They have to.

00:26:25.495 --> 00:26:26.830 align:middle line:90%
We have to.

00:26:26.830 --> 00:26:28.900 align:middle line:84%
So when you hear
from-- you have a lot

00:26:28.900 --> 00:26:34.240 align:middle line:84%
of followers of your work, a lot
of people that engage with you.

00:26:34.240 --> 00:26:36.910 align:middle line:84%
What would you say is the
general theme of the men that

00:26:36.910 --> 00:26:39.310 align:middle line:84%
are following your
work at this time?

00:26:39.310 --> 00:26:41.152 align:middle line:84%
What are the
reflections from them?

00:26:41.152 --> 00:26:42.610 align:middle line:84%
>>MARCUS: I think
it's men that are

00:26:42.610 --> 00:26:47.230 align:middle line:84%
interested in this
really robust life that

00:26:47.230 --> 00:26:48.860 align:middle line:90%
doesn't put them in one box.

00:26:48.860 --> 00:26:49.660 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:26:49.660 --> 00:26:51.490 align:middle line:84%
They're interested
in physical fitness.

00:26:51.490 --> 00:26:54.770 align:middle line:84%
They're interested in
performance out in business

00:26:54.770 --> 00:26:55.750 align:middle line:90%
and in their life.

00:26:55.750 --> 00:26:57.700 align:middle line:84%
But they're also
interested in cultivating

00:26:57.700 --> 00:27:00.670 align:middle line:84%
a true, felt,
experiential spirituality

00:27:00.670 --> 00:27:04.610 align:middle line:84%
and cultivating those softer,
feminine elements as well.

00:27:04.610 --> 00:27:07.150 align:middle line:84%
So I think that's
what I stand for.

00:27:07.150 --> 00:27:08.800 align:middle line:84%
And that's what
I've planted my flag

00:27:08.800 --> 00:27:11.590 align:middle line:84%
and talked about is the ability
to go to the extreme, like,

00:27:11.590 --> 00:27:14.020 align:middle line:84%
yeah, I can mix it
up in a boxing gym,

00:27:14.020 --> 00:27:16.060 align:middle line:90%
and I can go full out that way.

00:27:16.060 --> 00:27:21.160 align:middle line:84%
And I can also sit quietly in
a spiritual dieta in isolation

00:27:21.160 --> 00:27:23.470 align:middle line:84%
for 21 days or in
six-day darkness

00:27:23.470 --> 00:27:25.900 align:middle line:84%
retreat where it's just
me in the absolute silence

00:27:25.900 --> 00:27:27.040 align:middle line:90%
in the black.

00:27:27.040 --> 00:27:29.230 align:middle line:84%
I can do both of those
things and celebrate

00:27:29.230 --> 00:27:30.590 align:middle line:90%
both of those things.

00:27:30.590 --> 00:27:32.890 align:middle line:84%
And so the men, I
think, are feeling

00:27:32.890 --> 00:27:36.760 align:middle line:84%
free to actually live
their full birthright, live

00:27:36.760 --> 00:27:39.190 align:middle line:84%
that ability to express
themselves in all that way.

00:27:39.190 --> 00:27:41.800 align:middle line:84%
And I think the greatest
gift that any of us can give

00:27:41.800 --> 00:27:44.103 align:middle line:84%
is permission,
permission to exist.

00:27:44.103 --> 00:27:45.520 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So in a
sentence, what's

00:27:45.520 --> 00:27:47.980 align:middle line:84%
their greatest collective
frustration that they're

00:27:47.980 --> 00:27:50.770 align:middle line:84%
entering into engaging
with you and your work

00:27:50.770 --> 00:27:53.320 align:middle line:90%
with the collective expression?

00:27:53.320 --> 00:27:55.600 align:middle line:84%
>>MARCUS: It's being
out of balance.

00:27:55.600 --> 00:27:58.600 align:middle line:84%
I think it's hard to say that
there's one particular avatar

00:27:58.600 --> 00:28:00.700 align:middle line:84%
or archetype that
they're working with.

00:28:00.700 --> 00:28:04.120 align:middle line:84%
Some can't seem to
access that ability

00:28:04.120 --> 00:28:06.850 align:middle line:84%
to get their work
life in order or get

00:28:06.850 --> 00:28:09.280 align:middle line:84%
their physical body in order,
but they're really in tune.

00:28:09.280 --> 00:28:10.990 align:middle line:84%
They got a regular
meditation practice,

00:28:10.990 --> 00:28:12.940 align:middle line:84%
have done plenty of plant
medicine ceremonies.

00:28:12.940 --> 00:28:14.398 align:middle line:84%
And they're looking
to get from me,

00:28:14.398 --> 00:28:16.310 align:middle line:84%
hey, how do I get my
business plan together?

00:28:16.310 --> 00:28:18.190 align:middle line:84%
How do I get my body
in the right shape?

00:28:18.190 --> 00:28:21.050 align:middle line:84%
Other people, they've
got that figured out.

00:28:21.050 --> 00:28:21.900 align:middle line:90%
They know how.

00:28:21.900 --> 00:28:22.870 align:middle line:90%
They go to the gym every day.

00:28:22.870 --> 00:28:23.703 align:middle line:90%
They got a good job.

00:28:23.703 --> 00:28:25.390 align:middle line:84%
Maybe they exited
from a company.

00:28:25.390 --> 00:28:27.340 align:middle line:84%
And they're like I just
really want to find--

00:28:27.340 --> 00:28:29.470 align:middle line:84%
I feel like there's
something missing.

00:28:29.470 --> 00:28:32.800 align:middle line:84%
My spiritual self is
craving and calling.

00:28:32.800 --> 00:28:34.420 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So you
called it balance.

00:28:34.420 --> 00:28:34.960 align:middle line:90%
They're looking for balance.

00:28:34.960 --> 00:28:35.040 align:middle line:90%
>>MARCUS: Balance.

00:28:35.040 --> 00:28:35.980 align:middle line:90%
They're looking for balance.

00:28:35.980 --> 00:28:37.813 align:middle line:84%
Everybody's trying to
find that equilibrium.

00:28:37.813 --> 00:28:40.225 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So that brings us
to the subject of ayahuasca

00:28:40.225 --> 00:28:45.913 align:middle line:84%
and other psychotropic drugs and
what they bring to the table.

00:28:45.913 --> 00:28:47.080 align:middle line:90%
I've done a few shows on it.

00:28:47.080 --> 00:28:48.490 align:middle line:84%
Ben Stewart is
one of the fellows

00:28:48.490 --> 00:28:49.780 align:middle line:90%
that I've interviewed here.

00:28:49.780 --> 00:28:50.655 align:middle line:90%
>>MARCUS: He's great.

00:28:50.655 --> 00:28:52.510 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah,
he's really good.

00:28:52.510 --> 00:28:54.880 align:middle line:84%
And so from your
perspective, when

00:28:54.880 --> 00:28:59.230 align:middle line:84%
you started using
ayahuasca, what did you

00:28:59.230 --> 00:29:00.910 align:middle line:90%
find it opened up in you?

00:29:00.910 --> 00:29:03.460 align:middle line:84%
Because I've never
done ayahuasca.

00:29:03.460 --> 00:29:08.860 align:middle line:84%
I've done others-- I played
with other drugs ages ago--

00:29:08.860 --> 00:29:12.220 align:middle line:84%
mushrooms, LSD, did
everything a couple of times.

00:29:12.220 --> 00:29:14.630 align:middle line:84%
But I have a very different
response to all of them.

00:29:14.630 --> 00:29:18.670 align:middle line:84%
So I don't have a real sense of
what other people experience.

00:29:18.670 --> 00:29:21.850 align:middle line:84%
So what happens
with you and others

00:29:21.850 --> 00:29:26.760 align:middle line:84%
when it comes to these
kind of journeys you go on?

00:29:26.760 --> 00:29:31.360 align:middle line:84%
>>MARCUS: Every interaction with
a different medicine is unique.

00:29:31.360 --> 00:29:32.730 align:middle line:90%
There are some similarities.

00:29:32.730 --> 00:29:37.230 align:middle line:84%
Ayahuasca in particular is an
incredibly profound healer.

00:29:37.230 --> 00:29:39.090 align:middle line:90%
So on one hand the DMT--

00:29:39.090 --> 00:29:41.430 align:middle line:84%
which becomes orally active
through the combination

00:29:41.430 --> 00:29:43.800 align:middle line:84%
of the vine and the leaf
and how it's prepared,

00:29:43.800 --> 00:29:45.540 align:middle line:90%
and then the lineage--

00:29:45.540 --> 00:29:48.900 align:middle line:84%
that's going to immerse you
into this alternate reality,

00:29:48.900 --> 00:29:52.470 align:middle line:84%
this other universe of
beings and a felt sense

00:29:52.470 --> 00:29:54.480 align:middle line:84%
that I am in some
place that is very

00:29:54.480 --> 00:29:56.520 align:middle line:84%
different from the
normal waking world.

00:29:56.520 --> 00:29:58.360 align:middle line:84%
And information is
available to you

00:29:58.360 --> 00:30:00.360 align:middle line:84%
in a variety of different
ways through thoughts,

00:30:00.360 --> 00:30:01.800 align:middle line:90%
through visions.

00:30:01.800 --> 00:30:05.770 align:middle line:84%
And so that's happening for
that four to seven hours,

00:30:05.770 --> 00:30:08.070 align:middle line:84%
depending on how long
you're experiencing it.

00:30:08.070 --> 00:30:10.380 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time, you're
having a very physically

00:30:10.380 --> 00:30:11.880 align:middle line:90%
purgative process.

00:30:11.880 --> 00:30:15.450 align:middle line:84%
So the tea, which
is called the brew,

00:30:15.450 --> 00:30:17.250 align:middle line:84%
is moving its way
through your body.

00:30:17.250 --> 00:30:19.080 align:middle line:84%
And you're either
purging it through vomit

00:30:19.080 --> 00:30:22.108 align:middle line:84%
or purging it through the
other end or sometimes both.

00:30:22.108 --> 00:30:23.400 align:middle line:90%
They call that double platinum.

00:30:23.400 --> 00:30:25.290 align:middle line:84%
And I had a few episodes
of that where it's

00:30:25.290 --> 00:30:27.430 align:middle line:90%
out both ends at the same time.

00:30:27.430 --> 00:30:31.320 align:middle line:84%
So as you're kind of getting all
of this information downloaded

00:30:31.320 --> 00:30:33.510 align:middle line:84%
and this healing coming
through your psyche,

00:30:33.510 --> 00:30:36.120 align:middle line:84%
awareness of past traumas,
awareness of areas where you

00:30:36.120 --> 00:30:39.810 align:middle line:84%
may be out of alignment,
blessings from different beings

00:30:39.810 --> 00:30:42.158 align:middle line:84%
that are there, perhaps
they're our own imagination,

00:30:42.158 --> 00:30:44.700 align:middle line:84%
but they certainly don't feel
like it's our own imagination--

00:30:44.700 --> 00:30:47.040 align:middle line:84%
far beyond what we
could conceptualize--

00:30:47.040 --> 00:30:48.840 align:middle line:84%
these things coming
through, we're

00:30:48.840 --> 00:30:52.500 align:middle line:84%
also getting the physical
healing from that process.

00:30:52.500 --> 00:30:55.560 align:middle line:84%
And that I think is
the beauty of ayahuasca

00:30:55.560 --> 00:30:59.310 align:middle line:84%
in the right set, and setting,
with the right shaman.

00:30:59.310 --> 00:31:02.700 align:middle line:84%
Because it's ultimately a
very intense psychic surgery.

00:31:02.700 --> 00:31:05.700 align:middle line:84%
And it's something
that's not for everybody.

00:31:05.700 --> 00:31:09.210 align:middle line:84%
And it's a challenging
process, but it can yield

00:31:09.210 --> 00:31:11.822 align:middle line:90%
absolutely profound results.

00:31:11.822 --> 00:31:13.530 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I've always
wondered because it

00:31:13.530 --> 00:31:15.450 align:middle line:84%
seems to me what's
happening is you're opening

00:31:15.450 --> 00:31:17.170 align:middle line:90%
into other dimensional fields.

00:31:17.170 --> 00:31:21.330 align:middle line:84%
But depending on the types
of entities, and animals,

00:31:21.330 --> 00:31:23.040 align:middle line:84%
and such that
one's experiencing,

00:31:23.040 --> 00:31:25.990 align:middle line:84%
you don't know if you're going
into a lower dimensional field

00:31:25.990 --> 00:31:27.240 align:middle line:90%
or a higher dimensional field.

00:31:27.240 --> 00:31:29.010 align:middle line:84%
And it can be a
combination of both.

00:31:29.010 --> 00:31:31.570 align:middle line:84%
And it's not even fair to
say high and low, different--

00:31:31.570 --> 00:31:32.370 align:middle line:90%
>>MARCUS: Sure.

00:31:32.370 --> 00:31:35.610 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --more
elemental versus maybe

00:31:35.610 --> 00:31:38.767 align:middle line:84%
more oriented toward
angelic, you would say.

00:31:38.767 --> 00:31:40.350 align:middle line:84%
Some people feel
that they're entering

00:31:40.350 --> 00:31:43.810 align:middle line:84%
more angelic realms, others more
elemental from what everybody

00:31:43.810 --> 00:31:44.610 align:middle line:90%
tells me.

00:31:44.610 --> 00:31:48.000 align:middle line:84%
And one thing that
happens, I know

00:31:48.000 --> 00:31:51.480 align:middle line:84%
from just alcohol and
drug use in general,

00:31:51.480 --> 00:31:54.450 align:middle line:84%
is we can really kind of
make our auras, our fields,

00:31:54.450 --> 00:31:56.250 align:middle line:90%
very permeable.

00:31:56.250 --> 00:31:58.890 align:middle line:84%
And I think part of
the reason people

00:31:58.890 --> 00:32:01.350 align:middle line:84%
appear to be able to
move into other realms

00:32:01.350 --> 00:32:03.570 align:middle line:84%
and connect with these
different entities is

00:32:03.570 --> 00:32:05.280 align:middle line:90%
that exact permeability.

00:32:05.280 --> 00:32:07.530 align:middle line:84%
But what happens if
you're in the wrong hands?

00:32:07.530 --> 00:32:10.200 align:middle line:84%
And I ask because
someone very dear to me

00:32:10.200 --> 00:32:13.050 align:middle line:84%
had a very, very bad
experience in Ecuador

00:32:13.050 --> 00:32:15.490 align:middle line:84%
with what appears to be
not a very nice shaman.

00:32:15.490 --> 00:32:16.290 align:middle line:90%
>>MARCUS: Yeah.

00:32:16.290 --> 00:32:18.690 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Very bad, that
has lingering effects.

00:32:18.690 --> 00:32:20.580 align:middle line:84%
>>MARCUS: Well it's
the shaman's role.

00:32:20.580 --> 00:32:22.950 align:middle line:84%
What these maestros,
maestras, curanderos,

00:32:22.950 --> 00:32:25.500 align:middle line:84%
curanderas, what
they're trying to do

00:32:25.500 --> 00:32:28.230 align:middle line:84%
is create a field,
a collective field,

00:32:28.230 --> 00:32:31.380 align:middle line:84%
where those energies
from the outside

00:32:31.380 --> 00:32:34.980 align:middle line:84%
aren't able to basically
penetrate this bubble.

00:32:34.980 --> 00:32:37.410 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So their job is
to essentially protect,

00:32:37.410 --> 00:32:39.383 align:middle line:84%
to be alert because
they can see--

00:32:39.383 --> 00:32:40.800 align:middle line:84%
they should be
able to see or they

00:32:40.800 --> 00:32:43.230 align:middle line:84%
shouldn't be doing this
job if they're not seers.

00:32:43.230 --> 00:32:45.700 align:middle line:84%
And they should be able to know
how to protect and ward off

00:32:45.700 --> 00:32:46.500 align:middle line:90%
these entities.

00:32:46.500 --> 00:32:47.750 align:middle line:90%
>>MARCUS: They hold the space.

00:32:47.750 --> 00:32:48.760 align:middle line:90%
And that's their job.

00:32:48.760 --> 00:32:51.072 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes it's very
much like their gunslingers.

00:32:51.072 --> 00:32:52.530 align:middle line:84%
You'll see them
with their mapacho,

00:32:52.530 --> 00:32:53.940 align:middle line:90%
which is their sacred tobacco.

00:32:53.940 --> 00:32:55.650 align:middle line:84%
And they'll puff
and they'll go shhh.

00:32:55.650 --> 00:32:57.150 align:middle line:84%
And you know that
they're pushing,

00:32:57.150 --> 00:32:59.250 align:middle line:84%
they're pushing out those
energies or entities

00:32:59.250 --> 00:33:00.960 align:middle line:90%
out of the room.

00:33:00.960 --> 00:33:03.280 align:middle line:84%
And a really good
shaman will do that.

00:33:03.280 --> 00:33:06.660 align:middle line:84%
However, these darknesses
are within as well.

00:33:06.660 --> 00:33:09.040 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Exactly, finding
resonance with another.

00:33:09.040 --> 00:33:09.840 align:middle line:90%
>>MARCUS: Right.

00:33:09.840 --> 00:33:12.540 align:middle line:84%
So those things
can come up still

00:33:12.540 --> 00:33:14.880 align:middle line:84%
from within because the
shaman can't immediately

00:33:14.880 --> 00:33:17.220 align:middle line:84%
heal you and take all of
your darkness out of you.

00:33:17.220 --> 00:33:19.500 align:middle line:84%
So very often you will
encounter darkness.

00:33:19.500 --> 00:33:23.790 align:middle line:84%
So there are certain people
who, despite the great work

00:33:23.790 --> 00:33:26.500 align:middle line:84%
of the shamans, if they have
too much darkness within

00:33:26.500 --> 00:33:28.590 align:middle line:84%
and that darkness
is given license

00:33:28.590 --> 00:33:32.250 align:middle line:84%
to emerge too fast because
of the ayahuasca process,

00:33:32.250 --> 00:33:35.520 align:middle line:84%
there can be deeply challenging
experiences, psychoses,

00:33:35.520 --> 00:33:37.093 align:middle line:84%
different things
that can come up.

00:33:37.093 --> 00:33:39.510 align:middle line:84%
So you have to make sure that
your own darkness-- it would

00:33:39.510 --> 00:33:41.850 align:middle line:84%
be like if you have poison
in your system but the poison

00:33:41.850 --> 00:33:43.080 align:middle line:90%
is somewhat sequestered.

00:33:43.080 --> 00:33:45.690 align:middle line:84%
And you have something that's
going to melt that bubble

00:33:45.690 --> 00:33:47.880 align:middle line:84%
and then all of the poison
is going to be released,

00:33:47.880 --> 00:33:49.090 align:middle line:84%
you're going to have
to deal with that.

00:33:49.090 --> 00:33:51.600 align:middle line:84%
So you have to know that you're
really ready, that you're

00:33:51.600 --> 00:33:54.690 align:middle line:84%
called to this, and that you've
done enough work to know what

00:33:54.690 --> 00:33:58.920 align:middle line:84%
your poison pain bodies are
that are going to release even

00:33:58.920 --> 00:34:01.410 align:middle line:84%
despite the efficacy
of the shaman.

00:34:01.410 --> 00:34:02.560 align:middle line:90%
So that's one factor.

00:34:02.560 --> 00:34:05.070 align:middle line:84%
The other factor is maybe
the shaman isn't that good.

00:34:05.070 --> 00:34:08.190 align:middle line:84%
