00:36:26.320 --> 00:36:28.510 align:middle line:84%
it's just getting
you back to the state

00:36:28.510 --> 00:36:29.760 align:middle line:90%
of your natural being.

00:36:29.760 --> 00:36:30.560 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:36:30.560 --> 00:36:32.140 align:middle line:84%
And one point that
people don't generally

00:36:32.140 --> 00:36:34.515 align:middle line:84%
bring up, which is why I wanted
to talk to you about this

00:36:34.515 --> 00:36:37.960 align:middle line:84%
is the fact that you're calling
forth that own part of yourself

00:36:37.960 --> 00:36:40.810 align:middle line:84%
that's unhealed or
disowned by you,

00:36:40.810 --> 00:36:44.680 align:middle line:84%
which can call in resonant
forces of like energy.

00:36:44.680 --> 00:36:48.730 align:middle line:84%
So it's the two almost kind of
colluding and getting together

00:36:48.730 --> 00:36:50.560 align:middle line:84%
to play something
out while you're

00:36:50.560 --> 00:36:51.950 align:middle line:90%
in this very vulnerable state.

00:36:51.950 --> 00:36:54.130 align:middle line:84%
So I think what you
said is very valuable,

00:36:54.130 --> 00:36:55.640 align:middle line:90%
and I thank you for that.

00:36:55.640 --> 00:36:58.030 align:middle line:84%
So now let's go beyond
psychotropic drugs.

00:36:58.030 --> 00:37:00.100 align:middle line:90%
And let's go to darkness.

00:37:00.100 --> 00:37:02.600 align:middle line:84%
You talked about this darkness
retreat that you went on.

00:37:02.600 --> 00:37:04.850 align:middle line:84%
And I'd like to hear about
it in a little more detail.

00:37:04.850 --> 00:37:06.950 align:middle line:84%
So tell us what it's
like to be in the dark,

00:37:06.950 --> 00:37:08.030 align:middle line:90%
what, for seven days?

00:37:08.030 --> 00:37:09.033 align:middle line:90%
This was in Germany.

00:37:09.033 --> 00:37:11.200 align:middle line:84%
>>MARCUS: I ended up in
there for six days straight.

00:37:11.200 --> 00:37:11.800 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Six days.

00:37:11.800 --> 00:37:12.600 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:37:12.600 --> 00:37:13.750 align:middle line:90%
>>MARCUS: Yeah, in Germany.

00:37:13.750 --> 00:37:16.060 align:middle line:84%
You know when I talk
about this, I've

00:37:16.060 --> 00:37:17.680 align:middle line:84%
done a lot of
different things, this

00:37:17.680 --> 00:37:19.750 align:middle line:84%
was the thing that had
the most visceral reaction

00:37:19.750 --> 00:37:22.450 align:middle line:84%
to people where they were
like, I would never do that.

00:37:22.450 --> 00:37:24.130 align:middle line:84%
And you shouldn't
do that either.

00:37:24.130 --> 00:37:26.290 align:middle line:84%
People were projecting
their own fears onto me.

00:37:26.290 --> 00:37:30.310 align:middle line:84%
And it was interesting because
all it is is less than.

00:37:30.310 --> 00:37:31.498 align:middle line:90%
I'm not adding anything.

00:37:31.498 --> 00:37:33.040 align:middle line:84%
I'm actually just
subtracting things.

00:37:33.040 --> 00:37:35.260 align:middle line:84%
I'm subtracting light
in its entirety,

00:37:35.260 --> 00:37:36.580 align:middle line:90%
not a pinprick of light.

00:37:36.580 --> 00:37:39.730 align:middle line:84%
I'm subtracting experiences
with and interactions

00:37:39.730 --> 00:37:40.600 align:middle line:90%
with other people.

00:37:40.600 --> 00:37:42.130 align:middle line:90%
I'm completely alone.

00:37:42.130 --> 00:37:44.380 align:middle line:90%
And I'm subtracting sound.

00:37:44.380 --> 00:37:47.650 align:middle line:84%
You know silence,
darkness, and isolation,

00:37:47.650 --> 00:37:49.780 align:middle line:90%
but that idea was terrifying.

00:37:49.780 --> 00:37:52.630 align:middle line:84%
But it was curious to
me why is that so scary?

00:37:52.630 --> 00:37:53.590 align:middle line:90%
What are we afraid of?

00:37:53.590 --> 00:37:55.173 align:middle line:84%
Because the only
thing to be afraid of

00:37:55.173 --> 00:37:56.620 align:middle line:90%
is what we have inside.

00:37:56.620 --> 00:37:59.530 align:middle line:84%
And I think we have
a deep fear of what

00:37:59.530 --> 00:38:02.200 align:middle line:84%
is in the recesses
of our own psyche.

00:38:02.200 --> 00:38:04.543 align:middle line:84%
And until we meet
that fear, we're

00:38:04.543 --> 00:38:06.460 align:middle line:84%
not going to actually
be able to transcend it.

00:38:06.460 --> 00:38:08.380 align:middle line:84%
It's going to be
constantly in the shadows.

00:38:08.380 --> 00:38:10.240 align:middle line:84%
I liken it to
imagining that you're

00:38:10.240 --> 00:38:12.250 align:middle line:84%
afraid of a monster
under the bed,

00:38:12.250 --> 00:38:13.640 align:middle line:84%
but you never look
under the bed.

00:38:13.640 --> 00:38:15.265 align:middle line:84%
So every time you
get close to the bed,

00:38:15.265 --> 00:38:18.430 align:middle line:84%
you just dive onto the bed so
it doesn't nip at your heels.

00:38:18.430 --> 00:38:21.440 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So how did it progress
for you when you first went in?

00:38:21.440 --> 00:38:23.000 align:middle line:90%
I mean, obviously they fed you.

00:38:23.000 --> 00:38:23.800 align:middle line:90%
>>MARCUS: They do.

00:38:23.800 --> 00:38:26.530 align:middle line:84%
And they feed you through
a blacked out hallway

00:38:26.530 --> 00:38:27.430 align:middle line:90%
outside of the room.

00:38:27.430 --> 00:38:28.360 align:middle line:90%
They ring a little bell.

00:38:28.360 --> 00:38:29.890 align:middle line:84%
They mix up the times
that they feed you,

00:38:29.890 --> 00:38:31.307 align:middle line:84%
so you don't know
what time it is.

00:38:31.307 --> 00:38:34.630 align:middle line:84%
But food would arrive
and you would get fed.

00:38:34.630 --> 00:38:36.425 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So you had
the practical stuff.

00:38:36.425 --> 00:38:38.050 align:middle line:84%
And there's probably
somewhere a toilet

00:38:38.050 --> 00:38:38.980 align:middle line:90%
you can find your way to.

00:38:38.980 --> 00:38:39.610 align:middle line:90%
>>MARCUS: Toilet in there, yeah.

00:38:39.610 --> 00:38:40.652 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Basics covered.

00:38:40.652 --> 00:38:43.300 align:middle line:84%
Now what happens
psychologically?

00:38:43.300 --> 00:38:45.820 align:middle line:84%
>>MARCUS: Well you enter
into this alternate world.

00:38:45.820 --> 00:38:48.670 align:middle line:84%
You're out of the ordinary
world of life where you can see,

00:38:48.670 --> 00:38:50.260 align:middle line:84%
and you can talk,
and you can listen.

00:38:50.260 --> 00:38:51.802 align:middle line:84%
And you're just
there with your mind.

00:38:51.802 --> 00:38:54.190 align:middle line:84%
And the mind starts scrambling
for problems to solve.

00:38:54.190 --> 00:38:56.500 align:middle line:84%
And it starts to try and
figure everything out.

00:38:56.500 --> 00:38:58.480 align:middle line:90%
It was not relaxing at all.

00:38:58.480 --> 00:39:00.490 align:middle line:84%
This was not a
relaxing experience,

00:39:00.490 --> 00:39:02.260 align:middle line:84%
because the mind
goes into hyperdrive.

00:39:02.260 --> 00:39:04.180 align:middle line:84%
We like things to
distract ourselves.

00:39:04.180 --> 00:39:07.690 align:middle line:84%
It's like a rabid,
puzzle solving primate

00:39:07.690 --> 00:39:10.280 align:middle line:84%
that's just constantly trying
to work the Rubik's cube of life

00:39:10.280 --> 00:39:11.080 align:middle line:90%
but now--

00:39:11.080 --> 00:39:11.740 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: To stay in control.

00:39:11.740 --> 00:39:12.948 align:middle line:90%
>>MARCUS: To stay in control.

00:39:12.948 --> 00:39:15.040 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's
what the mind does.

00:39:15.040 --> 00:39:16.660 align:middle line:90%
The ego likes to solve problems.

00:39:16.660 --> 00:39:18.370 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The conscious,
what we call conscious mind.

00:39:18.370 --> 00:39:19.300 align:middle line:90%
>>MARCUS: Sure.

00:39:19.300 --> 00:39:21.478 align:middle line:84%
So then the first
few days I just tried

00:39:21.478 --> 00:39:23.020 align:middle line:84%
to solve all the
problems in my life.

00:39:23.020 --> 00:39:25.030 align:middle line:84%
And I determined that I
needed to move my house,

00:39:25.030 --> 00:39:28.270 align:middle line:84%
change my job, leave all
my partnerships, move away.

00:39:28.270 --> 00:39:31.090 align:middle line:84%
I was like going to be
a swashbuckling pirate

00:39:31.090 --> 00:39:32.780 align:middle line:90%
like sailing the seven seas.

00:39:32.780 --> 00:39:34.990 align:middle line:84%
It was just complete
fantasy about what

00:39:34.990 --> 00:39:37.840 align:middle line:84%
I needed to do compared
to what was reality.

00:39:37.840 --> 00:39:39.190 align:middle line:90%
And then as time progressed--

00:39:39.190 --> 00:39:40.840 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So once
you tick the list off

00:39:40.840 --> 00:39:44.030 align:middle line:84%
and you're a pirate on the
open seas, what was left?

00:39:44.030 --> 00:39:44.830 align:middle line:90%
>>MARCUS: Exactly.

00:39:44.830 --> 00:39:48.280 align:middle line:84%
So but then, ultimately, I
realized as time progressed,

00:39:48.280 --> 00:39:50.590 align:middle line:84%
my life is actually
perfect as it is.

00:39:50.590 --> 00:39:54.130 align:middle line:84%
And what's the challenge is
just getting a hold in my mind.

00:39:54.130 --> 00:39:57.520 align:middle line:84%
And the deep psychological
challenges of my mind

00:39:57.520 --> 00:40:02.770 align:middle line:84%
was a fear of really living and
enjoying life to the fullest

00:40:02.770 --> 00:40:06.610 align:middle line:84%
and loving the people in my
life, my partners, my mother,

00:40:06.610 --> 00:40:09.220 align:middle line:84%
in particular, all of the
different relationships

00:40:09.220 --> 00:40:11.410 align:middle line:84%
I had, really allowing
myself to surrender

00:40:11.410 --> 00:40:13.930 align:middle line:84%
to that beauty and
that love, because I

00:40:13.930 --> 00:40:15.520 align:middle line:90%
know that I have to give it up.

00:40:15.520 --> 00:40:18.460 align:middle line:84%
I know that time is going
to take all of this from me.

00:40:18.460 --> 00:40:23.090 align:middle line:84%
And I think a natural defense
mechanism that we all have is,

00:40:23.090 --> 00:40:26.110 align:middle line:84%
well, if I don't really allow
myself to love it that much,

00:40:26.110 --> 00:40:28.270 align:middle line:84%
when it goes away,
it won't hurt so bad.

00:40:28.270 --> 00:40:30.940 align:middle line:84%
So we're preparing ourself
for the disappointment

00:40:30.940 --> 00:40:34.660 align:middle line:84%
and the challenge of letting
go instead of just living

00:40:34.660 --> 00:40:37.180 align:middle line:84%
like that Warrior Poet that
I always strive to live for,

00:40:37.180 --> 00:40:39.190 align:middle line:84%
which is to love and
to live as fully as

00:40:39.190 --> 00:40:43.540 align:middle line:84%
possible despite the fact
that we have to let it all go.

00:40:43.540 --> 00:40:46.610 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: How was it for
you in terms of just--

00:40:46.610 --> 00:40:48.970 align:middle line:84%
could your mind let go
enough to even sleep?

00:40:48.970 --> 00:40:50.900 align:middle line:84%
I mean did you
have sleep cycles?

00:40:50.900 --> 00:40:53.185 align:middle line:84%
>>MARCUS: So at the start
you do sleep quite a bit,

00:40:53.185 --> 00:40:55.310 align:middle line:84%
because it's dark all the
time and you're sleeping.

00:40:55.310 --> 00:40:58.510 align:middle line:84%
And I had my aura ring on so
I was measuring my sleep even

00:40:58.510 --> 00:40:59.710 align:middle line:90%
though it was dark.

00:40:59.710 --> 00:41:01.030 align:middle line:90%
And I was sleeping pretty good.

00:41:01.030 --> 00:41:03.250 align:middle line:84%
And then an interesting
thing happens.

00:41:03.250 --> 00:41:05.225 align:middle line:84%
There's an endogenous
release of DMT

00:41:05.225 --> 00:41:06.850 align:middle line:84%
that occurs around
night three to five.

00:41:06.850 --> 00:41:08.985 align:middle line:84%
For me it's happening
around night three.

00:41:08.985 --> 00:41:10.360 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Such as
with ayahuasca.

00:41:10.360 --> 00:41:11.470 align:middle line:90%
>>MARCUS: Exactly.

00:41:11.470 --> 00:41:13.190 align:middle line:84%
But it's just
coming from within.

00:41:13.190 --> 00:41:17.800 align:middle line:84%
And I started to enter the
vision space around day three

00:41:17.800 --> 00:41:21.130 align:middle line:84%
and had incredibly potent
visions incessantly

00:41:21.130 --> 00:41:22.640 align:middle line:90%
for the next three days.

00:41:22.640 --> 00:41:25.630 align:middle line:84%
And during that time, I
was sleeping four hours,

00:41:25.630 --> 00:41:28.810 align:middle line:84%
three hours, finally two hours
a night of very light sleep

00:41:28.810 --> 00:41:31.920 align:middle line:84%
because I was immersed
in this visionscape.

00:41:31.920 --> 00:41:33.910 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: What were the visions?

00:41:33.910 --> 00:41:35.500 align:middle line:90%
What were they showing you?

00:41:35.500 --> 00:41:37.090 align:middle line:84%
What was the nature
of some of them?

00:41:37.090 --> 00:41:39.007 align:middle line:84%
>>MARCUS: Yeah, all kinds
of different things.

00:41:39.007 --> 00:41:41.620 align:middle line:84%
One really clear,
lucid vision that came

00:41:41.620 --> 00:41:44.200 align:middle line:90%
is I was really in a down state.

00:41:44.200 --> 00:41:47.290 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of challenging
